Mix of different conventions
Mix of Latin and Slavic conventions
In &lt;U+017D&gt;ejane dialect of Istro-Romanian, lur (Monday) and virer (Friday) follow the Latin convention, while utorek (Tuesday), sredu (Wednesday), and &lt;U+010D&gt;etrtok (Thursday) follow the Slavic convention.4













