Irregularities
Monday

After No Work
 After Bazaar
 Head of Week
 Master (as in Pir, because Muhammad was born on a Monday )
Tuesday

Thing (Assembly)  Second day of the week (cf. Hungarian kett&lt;U+0151&gt; &quot;two&quot;)
Wednesday

Mid-week or Middle
 The First Fast (Christianity)
Thursday

The day between two fasts (An D&lt;U+00E9&gt; idir dh&lt;U+00E1&gt; aoin, contracted to An D&lt;U+00E9&gt;ardaoin) (Christianity)
 Five (Arabic)
Friday

The Fast (Celtic) or Fasting Day (Icelandic) (Christianity)
 Good Friday or Preparation (Christianity)
 Day of Faith (Islam)
 Gathering/Assembly/Meeting (Islam)
 Half Weekend
Saturday

Shabbat or seventh-day Sabbath (Judeo&lt;U+2013&gt;Christian)
 Wash or Bath day
 Sun-eve (Eve of Sunday)
 After the Gathering (Islam)
 End of the Week (Arabic Sabt = End) (Islam)
